-- French Transaction Tax to Hurt Savers, Kessler Says in Echos
-- B y   F r a n k   C o n n e l l y
-- 2012-01-16T07:02:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-09/scor-chief-kessler-says-he-has-accomplished-mission-les-echos-reports.html
A tax on financial transactions
would mean lower returns for French holders of life insurance
contracts, as well as other savings and insurance products,  Scor
SE (SCR)  Chief Executive Officer Denis Kessler wrote in Les Echos.  The tax would drive up the cost of the numerous financial
transactions that are required to ensure the returns such
savings plans often provide, Kessler wrote.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at 
 fconnelly@bloomberg.net  